  simp only [runWithOracle_bind, ih]
  rfl
```

After `simp only [runWithOracle_bind, ih]`, the goal becomes:
`f ⟨(f (getPutativeRoot_with_hash s_left ...)) (f (getPutativeRoot_with_hash s_right ...)), (f (getPutativeRoot_with_hash s_right ...)) (f (getPutativeRoot_with_hash s_left ...))⟩ = ...`

The `rfl` tactic is then applied. `rfl` (reflexivity) proves goals of the form `t = t`. If the left and right sides of the equality are not definitionally equal, `rfl` will fail. In this case, the expressions are not definitionally equal, so `rfl` fails, leading to the "sorry" state because the proof term is missing.

The overall proof strategy is by induction on the `proof` list. This is a standard approach for lists. The induction hypothesis `ih` is `∀ (s : Skeleton) (idx : ...) (hv : ...) (hp : ...), runWithOracle f (getPutativeRoot s ... hp) = getPutativeRoot_with_hash s ... hp ...`.

