The proof needs to be constructed. We will use induction on the `proof` list.

```tactics
  induction proof with
  | nil =>
    simp [getPutativeRoot, getPutativeRoot_with_hash]
```

This handles the base case where the proof list is empty. `simp` will expand the definitions and show they are equal.

For the inductive step:

```tactics
  | cons h rest_proof ih =>
    simp [getPutativeRoot, getPutativeRoot_with_hash, runWithOracle] at ih ⊢
